Without the Corps…without the ring…without the willpower, what’s left is the Absolute Green Lantern!

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/766ba661-cc47-4808-a095-e359c1e7bdab/abglcov.jpg?format=original)

The Absolute Universe has been burning bright, and now it's expanding even further. Acclaimed writer Al Ewing (_Metamorpho: The Element Man, Immortal Hulk, Immortal Thor_) joins forces with artist Jahnoy Lindsay (_DC Power, Superboy: The Man of Tomorrow_) to deliver _Absolute Green Lantern_, a bold new take on Hal Jordan, John Stewart, Jo Mullein, and more. The series launches in comic book stores on Wednesday, April 2.

With _Absolute Batman, Absolute Superman_, and _Absolute Wonder Woman_ already cemented as essential reads, _Absolute Green Lantern_ is poised to be another standout. Ewing has a proven track record of breathing new life into characters and mythologies, as seen in his transformative work on _Hulk, Thor_, and _Venom_. At MegaCon 2025, Scott Snyder shared insights into the series, teasing a fresh approach to the Emerald Space Force—one that deviates from the ever-present cosmic authority of the standard DC Universe.

Be sure to check out the preview pages—this is one book you won’t want to miss!

